128  return ".";
129  }
130  size_t lastNotSlash = name.find_last_not_of('/');
131  // All '/'

133  return "/";
134  }
135  size_t leadingSlash = name.find_last_of('/', lastNotSlash);
136  // No '/'
137  if (leadingSlash == std::string::npos) {
138  return ".";
139  }
140  // dirname is '/'
141  if (leadingSlash == 0) {
142  return "/";
143  }
144  return name.substr(0, leadingSlash);
145 }

bool souffle::isInfixFunctorOp ( std::string_view  symbol)

Determines whether a functor should be written using infix notation (e.g.

a + b + c) or prefix notation (e.g. +(a,b,c))

Generally follow Haskell convention: functions w/ symbolic names are infix, otherwise prefix. NOTE: The surface syntax occasionally uses alpha infix operators For backwards compatibility we translate these into symbolic ops.

321  if (Global::config().has("output-dir") && !Global::config().has("output-dir", "-") &&
322  !existDir(Global::config().get("output-dir")) &&
323  !(Global::config().has("generate") ||
324  (Global::config().has("dl-program") && !Global::config().has("compile")))) {
325  throw std::runtime_error(
326  "output directory " + Global::config().get("output-dir") + " does not exists");
327  }
328 
329  /* collect all input directories for the c pre-processor */
330  if (Global::config().has("include-dir")) {
331  std::string currentInclude = "";
332  std::string allIncludes = "";
333  for (const char& ch : Global::config().get("include-dir")) {
334  if (ch == ' ') {
335  if (!existDir(currentInclude)) {
336  throw std::runtime_error("include directory " + currentInclude + " does not exists");
337  } else {
338  allIncludes += " -I";
339  allIncludes += currentInclude;
340  currentInclude = "";
341  }
342  } else {
343  currentInclude += ch;
344  }
345  }
346  allIncludes += " -I" + currentInclude;
347  Global::config().set("include-dir", allIncludes);
348  }
349 
350  /* collect all macro definitions for the pre-processor */
351  if (Global::config().has("macro")) {
352  std::string currentMacro = "";
353  std::string allMacros = "";
354  for (const char& ch : Global::config().get("macro")) {
355  if (ch == ' ') {
356  allMacros += " -D";
357  allMacros += currentMacro;
358  currentMacro = "";
359  } else {
360  currentMacro += ch;
361  }
362  }
363  allMacros += " -D" + currentMacro;
364  Global::config().set("macro", allMacros);
365  }
366 
367  /* turn on compilation of executables */
368  if (Global::config().has("dl-program")) {
369  Global::config().set("compile");
370  }
371 
372  if (Global::config().has("live-profile") && !Global::config().has("profile")) {
373  Global::config().set("profile");
374  }
375  } catch (std::exception& e) {
376  std::cerr << e.what() << std::endl;
377  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
378  }
379 
380  /**
381  * Ensure that code generation is enabled if using SWIG interface option.
382  */
383  if (Global::config().has("swig") && !Global::config().has("generate")) {
384  Global::config().set("generate", simpleName(Global::config().get("")));
385  }
386 
387  // ------ start souffle -------------
388 
389  std::string souffleExecutable = which(argv[0]);
390 
391  if (souffleExecutable.empty()) {
392  throw std::runtime_error("failed to determine souffle executable path");
393  }
394 
395  /* Create the pipe to establish a communication between cpp and souffle */
396  std::string cmd = ::which("mcpp");
397 
398  if (!isExecutable(cmd)) {
399  throw std::runtime_error("failed to locate mcpp pre-processor");
400  }
401 
402  cmd += " -e utf8 -W0 " + Global::config().get("include-dir");
403  if (Global::config().has("macro")) {
404  cmd += " " + Global::config().get("macro");
405  }
406  // Add RamDomain size as a macro
407  cmd += " -DRAM_DOMAIN_SIZE=" + std::to_string(RAM_DOMAIN_SIZE);
408  cmd += " " + Global::config().get("");
409  FILE* in = popen(cmd.c_str(), "r");
410 
411  /* Time taking for parsing */
412  auto parser_start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
413 
414  // ------- parse program -------------
415 
416  // parse file
417  ErrorReport errReport(Global::config().has("no-warn"));
418  DebugReport debugReport;

420  ParserDriver::parseTranslationUnit("<stdin>", in, errReport, debugReport);
421 
422  // close input pipe
423  int preprocessor_status = pclose(in);
424  if (preprocessor_status == -1) {
425  perror(nullptr);

427  }

430  if (Global::config().has("verbose")) {
431  auto parser_end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
432  std::cout << "Parse Time: " << std::chrono::duration<double>(parser_end - parser_start).count()
433  << "sec\n";

To souffle::ramBitCast ( From  source)

In C++20 there will be a new way to cast between types by reinterpreting bits (std::bit_cast), but as of January 2020 it is not yet supported.

Cast a type by reinterpreting its bits. Domain is restricted to Ram Types only. Template takes two types (second type is never necessary because it can be deduced from the argument) The following always holds For type T and a : T ramBitCast<T>(ramBitCast<RamDomain>(a)) == a
